** Max every level **<br>
MA<br>
Brawl<br>
Agility<br>
Strength<br>
Body Dev<br>
Intelligence<br>
<br>
** Max when I can get a new +damage/crit/heal nano**<br>
Bio Met<br>
Psy Mod<br>
Sen Imp<br>
Time Space<br>
<br>
** Points as neccessary for items **<br>
Treatment<br>
Comp lit<br>
Parry<br>
Dimach<br>
Perception<br>
 <br>
** Points as neccessary**<br>
Dodge<br>
Evade<br>
Duck <br>
Nano Resist<br>
Nano Pool<br>
Nano Init<br>
Dimach<br>
<br>
Is this the best approach to maximizing damage? in the short term? in the long term? What items should I be looking for to help me improve damage output? I do maximum cash on every mission, are there specific mission types or other sliders that I can move to produce more money and buy implants?<br>
<br>
I get one level for every 1.3 solo missions. I am getting by with implants/armor that I am finding in missions. I would buy implants, but missions don't seem to be generating enough cash to get to that magic 1M credits or more needed to buy even QL 100 implants. I am gaining about 50K a mission, so after 13 mission, I have 10 new levels, but only about 500K because I spend a fair amount on treatment kits and nano charges to minimize downtime. So ten levels later the implants that I was considering buying/building are starting to look a bit dated, and I could easily fit into better implants if I saved more money. The chasm between the money I have saved and the money to buy a full set of implants seems to be growing, not shrinking.<br>
<br>
Finally, when does leveling slow down? or does it? Someone told me that monsters start to toughen up at level 50, but I am now soloing stuff level 68. Of course, I have to fully heal health and nano after, but I can kill them to complete a mission and earn tokens.<br>
<br>
Thanks for any guidance, I know this is sort of general.<br>
<br>
